list-item.p:
The next aim is to carry out simulations under different operation conditions (working pressures and rotational velocities), for various pump operation strategies and pumping mechanisms:
no contact points (no teeth contact is studied in order to prove that, even if the interteeth radial clearance is sufficiently small, the leakage cannot be negligible);

all contact points (the ideal approach is considered with zero interteeth radial clearances used to model zero manufacturing tolerances);

one contact point at different locations (the existence of manufacturing tolerances and the teeth contact approach make the pump’s operation and its pumping mechanism more realistic in the simulation).
